name: Jcmd
tagline: Small tool that allows to switch JDK versions. It defines JDK_HOME/PATH variables and starts xterm on Linux/Unix and cmd.exe on Windows.
body:
JCMD
====

Small tool that allows to switch JDK versions. It defines JDK_HOME/PATH variables and starts xterm on Linux/Unix and cmd.exe on Windows.
note: Don't delete this file! It's used internally to help with page regeneration.
